South America
---
Chile (Arica). 18 Apr 2016. (reported) _Aedes aegypti_ found in Arica, a port about 1240 miles (2000 km) north of the Chilean capital, Santiago.
http://bigstory.ap.org/article/ae7b596c17374d97830e2dea6d0c4f04/mosquito-transmits-zika-found-chile
[Mainland Chile has been free of this vector mosquito until now. It is not clear whether this mosquito was found in several localities in this port city or just one. Implementation of control measures were not mentioned. - Mod.TY]

Ecuador. 21 Apr 2016. (reported) There is concern about increased risk of Zika virus infection in the areas affected by the recent earthquake. There, homes of 24 000 people have been destroyed or damaged, and municipal fresh water is unavailable. Emergency delivery of water may lead to water storage, providing breeding sites for the Zika virus vector mosquito.
http://news.trust.org/item/20160421123951-2dox7/?source=fiOtherNews2

Countries with cases but no ongoing transmission
